qas.question: How much did Seattle's foreign born population expand between 1990-2000?
From where in China did most of the first immigrants come?
How many Vietnamese residents are there in Seattle?
What is the population of Cambodian immigrants in Seattle?
What other group of people does Seattle have the largest percentage of in the US?

context: Seattle's foreign-born population grew <a0_0>40%<a0_0/> between the 1990 and 2000 censuses. The Chinese population in the Seattle area has origins in mainland China, Hong Kong, Southeast Asia, and Taiwan. The earliest Chinese-Americans that came in the late 19th and early 20th centuries were almost entirely from <a1_0>Guangdong province<a1_0/>. The Seattle area is also home to a large Vietnamese population of more than <a2_0>55,000<a2_0/> residents, as well as over 30,000 Somali immigrants. The Seattle-Tacoma area is also home to one of the largest Cambodian communities in the United States, numbering about <a3_0>19,000<a3_0/> Cambodian Americans, and one of the largest Samoan communities in the mainland U.S., with over 15,000 people having Samoan ancestry. Additionally, the Seattle area had the highest percentage of <a4_0>self-identified mixed-race<a4_0/> people of any large metropolitan area in the United States, according to the 2000 United States Census Bureau. According to a 2012 HistoryLink study, Seattle's 98118 ZIP code (in the Columbia City neighborhood) was one of the most diverse ZIP Code Tabulation Areas in the United States.
